cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with video object trajectory classification and anomaly detection using neural networks, which is a problem related to computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a hybrid CNN-VAE architecture, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The use of semi-supervised learning and clustering algorithms for trajectory labeling and anomaly detection suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with video data, which falls under the scope of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with surveillance video datasets and anomaly detection, which may also make cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category.
